      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is a powerful judicial tool that allows courts to protect fundamental rights not explicitly listed in the Constitution, such as privacy and bodily autonomy. This concept has been used to expand civil liberties by striking down oppressive laws and ensuring the government respects individual dignity against state overreach. By interpreting the Fourteenth Amendment broadly, the Supreme Court has consistently empowered citizens to define their own lives free from unjustified government interference.",
